   Discard after pulling the top-symbol report.)

Top symbols report (after the above):
  /home/lilith/bin/perf report --stdio -i perf.data --no-children \
    --percent-limit 0.5

NOTE: do not enable `-C target-cpu=native` (per CLAUDE.md
"Performance Optimization" section). The encoder ships through
runtime SIMD dispatch; `native` bakes ISAs that production users
may not have.

DO NOT cite "FMA precision" for any wall-time delta — the SIMD
chain agent's wins should be reported as alloc/SIMD/scratch
savings, never as FMA precision changes (per W44-66 user
correction).
